&lt;p&gt;Are you an a registered anesthetic practitioner with at least two years’ experience at band 6 level? Are you looking for the next step up in your career? Do you want to work in a London major trauma centre? Are you a born leader?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have answered yes to all of these questions, then we want to hear from you. We are looking for an experienced senior anesthetic practitioner to manage our anesthetic support team at the Royal London Hospital. You will have the opportunity to develop your management skills while maintaining your clinical skills. You will be managing a large team in theatres but will also have the opportunity to learn how to coordinate the theatre activity through our very busy department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the Royal London we have a commitment to provide ongoing professional and educational development. We are a forward thinking team and we are striving to build a dynamic and enthusiastic senior management team. If you are up for the challenge and would like further information please contact Anne Gully, Matron on 02035940366 or email a.gully@nhs.net.&lt;/p&gt;
